- Active alerts are those with a status of 'active';
- Performance metrics include average CPU utilization, memory used, and NVMe total utilization;
- Recent user accesses are those that occurred within the last week.

- Active alerts are those that are currently unresolved or ongoing;
- Alert types can include issues such as high CPU usage or low memory;
- The alert time is a timestamp indicating when the alert was generated.

- 'Sounding the medium-level alarms' refers to alerts with a severity level of 'medium';
- 'Currently' refers to alerts with a status of 'active';
- 'Vast digital forest' is a metaphor for the network of servers and their performance metrics.

- "top 5 most active users" refers to users with the highest number of accesses to performance metrics;
- "garden of server metrics" is a metaphor for the database containing server performance data;
- "flowers of performance" represents the performance metrics;
- "nourished by their frequent visits" indicates that users who access the metrics frequently are considered active;
- "last drops of dew" refers to the last time a user accessed a metric;
- "average health of the garden" is a metaphor for the average utilization metrics (NVMe, CPU, memory) of the servers;
- "monitor" implies that these metrics are observed and recorded by the users.

- 'Gardeners' refers to the users who accessed the server;
- 'Vital signs' refers to the CPU utilization of the server;
- 'Glanced at' means the users viewed the server's metrics;
- 'Brief moment' indicates the specific time interval from '2023-10-01 12:00:00' to '2023-10-01 12:01:00'.

- "Working the hardest" refers to servers with the highest average CPU utilization;
- "During the month of September 2023" corresponds to the date range from '2023-09-01' to '2023-10-01';
- CPU utilization is a measure of how much of the CPU's processing power is being used at any given time.

- "frequent visitors" refers to users who have accessed performance metrics more than 5 times;
- "garden of performance metrics" is a metaphor for the system's performance metrics data;
- "tended to the garden" means accessing or interacting with the performance metrics.
